The paper deals with efficient algorithms for computing spectral sketches of Laplacian matrices, which are commonly used in various areas of computer science such as data analysis, machine learning, and network analysis. The paper also mentions the computation of effective resistances, which is a topic related to graph algorithms and network analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG) to some extent, so they are also possible sub-categories.
